53:30.268 --> 53:32.061
Mr. McAllister,
we've worked together

53:32.182 --> 53:34.351
on the S.G.A. for 3 solid years.

53:34.487 --> 53:36.447
Besides, my own best banner
was torn down.

53:36.618 --> 53:37.911
Did I do that, too?

53:38.010 --> 53:39.345
Were you or were you not

53:39.489 --> 53:41.324
working in the Looking Glass Office

53:41.490 --> 53:42.407
over the weekend?

53:42.490 --> 53:46.077
I was. So?
Mr. Paterno let me in.

53:46.317 --> 53:48.486
As you know, with my
many responsibilities,

53:48.667 --> 53:50.085
I often have to come in
on the weekend.

53:50.188 --> 53:52.149
And I have permission to do so.

53:52.320 --> 53:54.906
But I left very early,
around 6:30.

53:56.278 --> 53:59.865
6:30. 6:30?

54:00.106 --> 54:02.608
How do you know what time
the posters were torn down?

54:02.803 --> 54:05.347
I don't. I just know

54:05.542 --> 54:06.960
that they were there when I left.

54:07.108 --> 54:09.444
I'm giving you helpful
information, that's all.

54:09.588 --> 54:10.548
You know, instead
of wasting your time

54:10.675 --> 54:11.634
interrogating me,

54:12.981 --> 54:13.773
we should be out there

54:13.851 --> 54:14.977
trying to figure out
who did this.

54:15.069 --> 54:17.196
OK, Tracy.

54:17.330 --> 54:18.915
Who do you think did it?

54:19.070 --> 54:20.905
Whom should we interrogate?

54:21.028 --> 54:22.696
Well, I don't know.

54:22.853 --> 54:24.188
You know, it could
have been anybody.

54:24.332 --> 54:26.626
There's a lot of subversive
elements here at Carver,

54:26.812 --> 54:30.274
like Rick Thiessen or
Kevin Speck and those burnouts.

54:30.509 --> 54:31.552
Or what about Tammy Metzler?

54:31.683 --> 54:32.601
I mean, her whole thing

54:32.683 --> 54:34.894
is being anti-this and anti-that.

54:36.467 --> 54:39.512
Tracy, you're
a very intelligent girl.

54:39.729 --> 54:42.524
You have a lot of
admirable qualities.

54:42.687 --> 54:44.522
But one day maybe you'll learn

54:44.689 --> 54:45.690
that being smart

54:45.819 --> 54:48.364
and doing whatever you
need to do to get ahead

54:48.559 --> 54:50.060
and, yes, stepping
on other people

54:50.212 --> 54:51.463
to get there,

54:51.560 --> 54:55.147
well, there's a whole lot
more to life than that.

54:55.388 --> 54:57.891
And, in the end, you're
only cheating yourself.

54:59.216 --> 55:01.301
Why are you lecturing me?

55:01.477 --> 55:05.857
This isn't the time or
the place to get into it.

55:06.131 --> 55:08.342
But there is,
for just one example,

55:08.524 --> 55:10.443
a certain former colleague of mine

55:10.567 --> 55:14.113
who made a very big mistake,
a life mistake.

55:14.352 --> 55:15.728
Now, I think
the lesson here is that,

55:15.875 --> 55:19.420
old or young,
we all make mistakes.

55:19.658 --> 55:21.452
